1. The Hydrological Cycle (Water Cycle)
The hydrological cycle (water cycle) describes the continuous movement of water through the Earth's systems
– atmosphere, surface, and subsurface. It is driven by solar energy (for evaporation) and gravity (for precipitation
and runoff). It has NO beginning or end – it is a perpetual cycle.
