1.4 Water Balance Equation
Water Balance (Continuity Equation)
P = ET + Q + DS
Where:
P = Precipitation (total input)
ET = Evapotranspiration (losses to atmosphere)
Q = Streamflow/Runoff (outflow from catchment)
DS = Change in storage (soil moisture + groundwater)
Global average: P(land) = 111,000 km³/yr; ET = 71,000 km³/yr; Q = 40,000 km³/yr
1.5 Residence Time
Residence Time (t) = Volume of reservoir / Rate of inflow (or outflow). It indicates how long a water molecule
spends in a reservoir on average. Atmosphere: ~9 days; Rivers: ~16 days; Lakes: years; Glaciers: thousands of
years; Deep groundwater: up to 10,000 years. Environmental significance: long residence time means slow
recovery if contaminated (e.g., groundwater pollution is nearly irreversible).
n EXAM TIP: Water cycle quantities: Precipitation over oceans = 385,000 km³/yr; over land = 111,000
km³/yr. River runoff to ocean = ~40,000 km³/yr. Atmospheric water residence time = 9–10 days. The
DRIVING FORCE of the water cycle is solar energy (for evaporation) + gravity (for precipitation/runoff).
Penman–Monteith is the standard equation for reference ET calculation.
