4.5 Temperature Correction for BOD
BOD rate constant (k_d) varies with temperature. Van't Hoff–Arrhenius equation is simplified for water quality to:
Temperature Correction
k_d(T) = k_d(20°C) × q^(T-20)
Where q (theta) = temperature coefficient = 1.047 (for BOD)
Example: k_d at 25°C = 0.23 × 1.047^(25-20) = 0.23 × 1.259 = 0.29 dayn¹
Higher temperature ® faster BOD ® more rapid On depletion in summer
